Permissions are user group-level access rights to various features in the Cloud Provisioning and Governance application and to specific records in the instance, such as a blueprint or a cloud account. 

]]>
false d9e3789c93c13200bebe7344967ffb1e false true
  • In the Cloud Admin portal, navigate Govern > Permission.  
  • Click New. 
  • Fill out the form fields and click Submit. 

    •              

     Field

     Description

     All entities 

     Select this option to apply the permission to all records in the table. 

     Group 

     Select the user group to which the permissions will apply. 

     Permission 

     Select the permission type:  

     Access [Read]: Users can see the record, but not edit or delete. 

     Manage [Create & Update]: Users can see the record and create and update new records in the same table, but cannot delete any records. 

     Delete: Users can delete specified records or all records in the table. 

     Execute: Users can execute an action on records in the table. 

     All: Users have permissions on all records in the table. 

     Target Type 

     Select the cloud table in which the target record belongs. 

     Target Entity 

     Select the record that the permission is based upon. This field does not appear if you select All Entities.
